1
00:00:11,116 --> 00:00:13,118
[rock music playing]

2
00:00:43,649 --> 00:00:45,359
[boss] Do you like jjajangmyeon that much?

3
00:00:45,442 --> 00:00:46,777
CHAPTER 36:
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

4
00:00:46,861 --> 00:00:48,571
-I remember how much you like it.
-Yes, boss.

5
00:00:48,654 --> 00:00:50,239
-Is it good?
-[chuckling]

6
00:00:55,286 --> 00:00:56,829
[Eui-ju gasps] Mr. Ga! [gasps]

7
00:00:56,912 --> 00:00:58,414
[whimpers] Are you okay?

8
00:00:58,497 --> 00:01:00,499
-[groans]
-Oh, no.

9
00:01:00,583 --> 00:01:01,584
Are you okay?

10
00:01:01,667 --> 00:01:03,711
[gasps] I'm sorry. Oh, my, Mr. Ga.

11
00:01:03,794 --> 00:01:05,462
Oh, my goodness, Mr. Ga.

12
00:01:05,546 --> 00:01:07,965
What are these beautiful
angels doing here?

13
00:01:08,048 --> 00:01:09,049
[thugs chuckling]

14
00:01:09,133 --> 00:01:12,720
What brings such a divine presence
to this humble place?

15
00:01:13,304 --> 00:01:16,765
Did you do that to our boy right there?

16
00:01:17,349 --> 00:01:19,810
-Yeah. [chuckles]
-[Eui-ju] Oh, my goodness, Mr. Ga.

17
00:01:19,894 --> 00:01:21,395
[boss chuckling] Well, now.

18
00:01:21,896 --> 00:01:23,606
Guess what, boys.

19
00:01:23,689 --> 00:01:25,566
We have guests in the house.

20
00:01:25,649 --> 00:01:28,319
Don't just sit back there.
Bring them some welcome drinks.

21
00:01:28,402 --> 00:01:29,403
Oh, man.

22
00:01:29,486 --> 00:01:30,738
Stay with the kids.

23
00:01:31,572 --> 00:01:32,656
Should we?

24
00:01:32,740 --> 00:01:34,950
-[boss chuckles]
-[Eui-ju whimpers]

25
00:01:35,034 --> 00:01:36,035
Good luck.

26
00:01:37,786 --> 00:01:38,829
Did they hit you?

27
00:01:41,624 --> 00:01:43,459
-Mr. Dong-ju--
-Nah, he's all right. Don't worry.

28
00:01:43,542 --> 00:01:45,002
He's going to be okay.

29
00:01:45,085 --> 00:01:46,754
Is this fun for you?

30
00:01:49,214 --> 00:01:50,424
Picking on kids?

31
00:01:51,133 --> 00:01:52,134
[sighs]

32
00:01:53,093 --> 00:01:54,595
-[Gi-jeon] Damn.
-[coughs]

33
00:01:57,014 --> 00:01:58,015
[sighs]

34
00:01:58,599 --> 00:02:01,352
-Oh, you little annoying bastards.
-Teach him a lesson.

35
00:02:02,061 --> 00:02:03,562
-[blow lands]
-[groans]

36
00:02:03,646 --> 00:02:05,648
-Holy--
-What? W-What the hell?

37
00:02:05,731 --> 00:02:06,732
Hey!

38
00:02:07,441 --> 00:02:09,109
[heroic rock music playing]

39
00:02:09,193 --> 00:02:10,569
[thug groans]

40
00:02:13,030 --> 00:02:13,989
Hey!

41
00:02:14,949 --> 00:02:16,075
[sighs]

42
00:02:17,993 --> 00:02:19,244
[thug] That crazy little…

43
00:02:19,328 --> 00:02:20,329
[grunts]

44
00:02:20,412 --> 00:02:21,413
Boys, let's get him!

45
00:02:22,623 --> 00:02:24,750
[grunting]

46
00:02:26,585 --> 00:02:27,586
[yelling]

47
00:02:29,296 --> 00:02:30,673
-Hey!
-[grunting]

48
00:02:30,756 --> 00:02:31,757
There you go!

49
00:02:33,425 --> 00:02:34,677
Damn it!

50
00:02:38,180 --> 00:02:39,181
That's right!

51
00:02:40,140 --> 00:02:41,725
What are you doing? [gasps]

52
00:02:41,809 --> 00:02:43,102
[grunts]

53
00:02:43,185 --> 00:02:45,521
Are you okay, man?
Yeah, yeah, you're okay.

54
00:02:58,951 --> 00:03:00,202
-[boss] Look at you.
-Hold on.

55
00:03:00,285 --> 00:03:03,288
[boss] Hey, hey, hey. Oh, man.
Can a teacher be this good at fighting?

56
00:03:03,372 --> 00:03:04,999
-[whimpers]
-Teacher…

57
00:03:08,168 --> 00:03:09,169
[boss grunts]

58
00:03:10,254 --> 00:03:11,547
[Eui-ju gasps]

59
00:03:12,423 --> 00:03:14,299
[groans] Damn.

60
00:03:14,383 --> 00:03:17,052
[groaning]

61
00:03:17,970 --> 00:03:19,304
[exclaims]

62
00:03:22,725 --> 00:03:26,729
[panting] Who the hell are you?

63
00:03:27,896 --> 00:03:29,898
Me? A literature teacher.

64
00:03:31,275 --> 00:03:34,111
Whoa, a literature teacher. Damn it!

65
00:03:34,987 --> 00:03:36,780
[shirt ripping]

66
00:03:40,617 --> 00:03:43,662
[dramatic techno music playing]

67
00:03:49,918 --> 00:03:51,086
[gasps]

68
00:03:54,715 --> 00:03:55,716
No, don't. Don't.

69
00:03:59,219 --> 00:04:01,055
[whispering] Here, let's go. Come on.

70
00:04:05,350 --> 00:04:07,686
EPISODE 12

71
00:04:07,770 --> 00:04:08,771
[music fades]

72
00:04:08,854 --> 00:04:10,272
How are you going to fix this?

73
00:04:10,898 --> 00:04:12,566
We'll pretend it never happened. [laughs]

74
00:04:13,484 --> 00:04:15,319
Apologize to the students.

75
00:04:17,654 --> 00:04:18,781
-We're sorry.
-We're sorry.

76
00:04:21,116 --> 00:04:22,451
Are you gonna show up again?

77
00:04:23,077 --> 00:04:24,161
-No, sir.
-No, sir.

78
00:04:24,745 --> 00:04:26,246
No, we won't.

79
00:04:26,914 --> 00:04:28,332
If I see your faces again,

80
00:04:29,166 --> 00:04:30,918
you'll be dead meat for real.

81
00:04:32,086 --> 00:04:33,087
[sighs]

82
00:04:33,170 --> 00:04:35,672
[boss] Oh, uh, a shaman once told me that

83
00:04:35,756 --> 00:04:38,258
I'd live a long life. [chuckles, sighs]

84
00:04:38,342 --> 00:04:39,843
[comical, awkward music playing]

85
00:04:39,927 --> 00:04:41,303
[groans]

86
00:04:43,388 --> 00:04:44,681
Goodbye then, Teach.

87
00:04:45,265 --> 00:04:47,976
Uh, I mean, Mr. Teacher, sir. [chuckles]

88
00:04:49,436 --> 00:04:50,562
[sighs] Let's go now.

89
00:04:53,065 --> 00:04:54,066
[Da-ju] Let's go.

90
00:05:01,115 --> 00:05:04,368
[groaning]

91
00:05:04,451 --> 00:05:05,786
Oh, fuck!

92
00:05:05,869 --> 00:05:07,871
What the hell's wrong with that guy?

93
00:05:08,497 --> 00:05:10,541
A literature teacher? Huh?

94
00:05:10,624 --> 00:05:12,167
Can a literature teacher do that?

95
00:05:13,252 --> 00:05:15,129
He was actually being serious

96
00:05:15,754 --> 00:05:18,590
when he said we'd be dead
if he saw our faces again.

97
00:05:20,342 --> 00:05:23,512
The look in his eyes.
I could tell he meant it when he said it.

98
00:05:24,096 --> 00:05:26,682
[Yeong-jae] What? Who are they?
What if they kidnapped her?

99
00:05:26,765 --> 00:05:29,476
[Dan-ji] What fancy people?
She lives at a shelter.

100
00:05:30,018 --> 00:05:32,271
-[operator] The number you dialed cannot…
-Why wouldn't she pick up?

101
00:05:32,354 --> 00:05:33,522
CHAPTER 37:
UNMASKED FOR JUSTICE

102
00:05:33,605 --> 00:05:35,232
Why is she not even checking her phone?

103
00:05:35,315 --> 00:05:37,818
[inhales sharply, sighs]

104
00:05:37,901 --> 00:05:39,570
[line ringing]

105
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,459
Geez.

106
00:05:57,296 --> 00:05:59,339
[breathes shakily]

107
00:06:00,716 --> 00:06:03,635
[tender music playing]

108
00:06:13,979 --> 00:06:15,063
Darn you!

109
00:06:17,024 --> 00:06:18,275
Seriously?

110
00:06:19,067 --> 00:06:21,778
I was so worried about you. [whimpers]

111
00:06:22,571 --> 00:06:24,781
It was already scary
knowing Ji-a was in danger,

112
00:06:24,865 --> 00:06:26,283
but I couldn't reach you either.

113
00:06:26,366 --> 00:06:29,369
I wondered if you got involved in it,
or if something bad was happening.

114
00:06:29,453 --> 00:06:30,996
I got all kinds of ideas.

115
00:06:31,079 --> 00:06:33,332
[whimpers] Geez.

116
00:06:34,208 --> 00:06:36,960
You didn't answer my calls
or even check my texts.

117
00:06:39,087 --> 00:06:40,839
None of the girls knew
what you were up to.

118
00:06:40,923 --> 00:06:42,883
I was scared to death alone.
You know that?

119
00:06:43,884 --> 00:06:45,385
[sobbing]

120
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:48,430
I have a crush on Math.

121
00:06:52,893 --> 00:06:54,353
[sniffles]

122
00:06:54,895 --> 00:06:55,896
Huh?

123
00:06:57,814 --> 00:07:01,568
I could've just told you
that I started to have a crush on Math,

124
00:07:02,527 --> 00:07:04,154
but I couldn't open up to you.

125
00:07:05,072 --> 00:07:08,659
I thought you'd find it stupid because
we used to bad-mouth him all the time,

126
00:07:08,742 --> 00:07:10,661
and I was feeling lost myself

127
00:07:11,411 --> 00:07:12,788
with all these emotions.

128
00:07:13,705 --> 00:07:16,792
And then, I just hurt your feelings.

129
00:07:17,834 --> 00:07:18,835
I'm sorry.

130
00:07:24,132 --> 00:07:27,386
What made me sad was knowing that
you were keeping a secret from me.

131
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:30,931
I don't even care
if you have a crush on Dong-ju.

132
00:07:31,765 --> 00:07:34,893
But I was just upset because
you weren't opening up to me.

133
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:41,108
You used to share
every little detail with me.

134
00:07:42,734 --> 00:07:45,737
Even when you were constipated,
I was the first to know.

135
00:07:51,994 --> 00:07:54,663
You come before anyone else to me.
You know that.

136
00:07:57,291 --> 00:07:58,292
[sniffles]

137
00:08:00,085 --> 00:08:01,086
So…

138
00:08:01,795 --> 00:08:06,174
If Mr. Dong-ju and I were both drowning,
who would you save first?

139
00:08:08,427 --> 00:08:10,971
You used to compete
in baby swimming contests.

140
00:08:13,849 --> 00:08:14,850
You're silly.

141
00:08:15,934 --> 00:08:16,935
[chuckles]

142
00:08:17,769 --> 00:08:19,688
Anyway, did something really happen?

143
00:08:23,233 --> 00:08:25,777
You're not gonna believe me
even if I tell you.

144
00:08:25,861 --> 00:08:26,987
What is it?

145
00:08:27,070 --> 00:08:28,071
Come on. Tell me.

146
00:08:29,364 --> 00:08:31,783
-At first, all those gangsters…
-[chuckles]

147
00:08:31,867 --> 00:08:34,328
-…totally looked down on him.
-Mm-hmm. Uh-huh.

148
00:08:34,411 --> 00:08:36,997
You know, they were kind of like,
"Who's this wimp?"

149
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:38,081
And then?

150
00:08:38,165 --> 00:08:41,835
But then, he just looked at them ice-cold.

151
00:08:41,918 --> 00:08:44,463
His voice wasn't that gentle voice
he usually uses with us.

152
00:08:44,546 --> 00:08:46,673
-Mm-hmm. [giggles]
-He looked at them and said,

153
00:08:47,924 --> 00:08:49,926
"Is it fun picking on kids?"

154
00:08:50,010 --> 00:08:51,303
[gasps] Oh, man.

155
00:08:51,386 --> 00:08:53,930
I got goose bumps all over, all over!

156
00:08:54,014 --> 00:08:55,682
Then he just started beating them up

157
00:08:55,766 --> 00:08:58,477
with a front kick, and a back kick
and a flying kick!

158
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:00,771
He grabbed them by the collar
and threw punches like…

159
00:09:00,854 --> 00:09:02,481
like a movie. Bam! Bam!

160
00:09:02,564 --> 00:09:04,900
He beat every one of them.
There wasn't even one standing.

161
00:09:04,983 --> 00:09:06,568
-And then…
-Uh-huh?

162
00:09:06,651 --> 00:09:09,363
And then… his shirt got ripped.

163
00:09:09,446 --> 00:09:10,447
It got ripped?

164
00:09:10,530 --> 00:09:13,075
[gasps] You know the Medusa, right?

165
00:09:13,158 --> 00:09:15,744
It was right there
with all the snakes coiled up.

166
00:09:15,827 --> 00:09:18,330
The whole image, the whole thing.
You know what I'm saying?

167
00:09:18,413 --> 00:09:21,458
[gasps] And there's also this massive
dragon-like creature all the way across.

168
00:09:21,541 --> 00:09:22,793
It was huge!

169
00:09:23,377 --> 00:09:24,378
Dong-ju…

170
00:09:25,420 --> 00:09:26,421
uh…

171
00:09:27,089 --> 00:09:29,216
has a tattoo? [gasps]

172
00:09:29,299 --> 00:09:30,300
Yeah.

173
00:09:30,842 --> 00:09:33,720
And also, it looked pretty old
with the ink a bit faded,

174
00:09:34,346 --> 00:09:36,223
but it was definitely Medusa.

175
00:09:36,973 --> 00:09:41,853
Uh, and it seemed like it stretched
all the way from the shoulder to the back,

176
00:09:41,937 --> 00:09:43,397
but I didn't get to see his back.

177
00:09:43,897 --> 00:09:47,109
Huh. Then Dong-ju's…

178
00:09:47,192 --> 00:09:48,360
[inhales sharply]

179
00:09:48,985 --> 00:09:52,614
I think maybe…
I think that he used to be a gangster.

180
00:09:57,244 --> 00:09:59,621
[amusing music playing]

181
00:10:02,624 --> 00:10:03,875
A-Are you okay?

182
00:10:07,462 --> 00:10:11,049
You're saying
Dong-ju used to be a gangster?

183
00:10:20,225 --> 00:10:21,935
[softly] I shouldn't have told her.

184
00:10:22,727 --> 00:10:25,313
-[Woo-su groans] Wait, wait!
-[Gi-jeon] I didn't even touch you yet.

185
00:10:25,814 --> 00:10:27,274
Wait, wait, wait, wait! Just wait.

186
00:10:27,357 --> 00:10:29,109
-Brace yourself.
-[groaning]

187
00:10:29,192 --> 00:10:30,569
-Hold still.
-Put some on his lips too.

188
00:10:30,652 --> 00:10:31,736
-Hold still.
-[Woo-su whining]

189
00:10:31,820 --> 00:10:34,072
-I'm almost done.
-Stop, stop. It hurts. [groans]

190
00:10:34,156 --> 00:10:35,574
-I'll put a bandage on later.
-It hurts.

191
00:10:35,657 --> 00:10:38,368
This is ridiculous. Ugh.
He's driving me insane, seriously.

192
00:10:38,452 --> 00:10:39,744
Let me see your hands.

193
00:10:39,828 --> 00:10:41,830
Geez. Your hands are a total mess.

194
00:10:43,748 --> 00:10:46,376
-This part is okay at least.
-[Dong-ju sighs]

195
00:10:49,838 --> 00:10:50,839
[groans]

196
00:10:50,922 --> 00:10:52,007
[Gi-jeon] Are you all right?

197
00:10:54,509 --> 00:10:56,636
I was never going to
get into a fight again.

198
00:10:59,598 --> 00:11:00,891
But this happened.

199
00:11:02,225 --> 00:11:03,477
[sighs]

200
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:05,145
And in front of my students too.

201
00:11:05,228 --> 00:11:06,271
[inhales sharply]

202
00:11:06,354 --> 00:11:07,939
-[sighs]
-It was inevitable though.

203
00:11:09,608 --> 00:11:10,901
They even saw my tattoo.

204
00:11:13,820 --> 00:11:16,281
[groans] What do I do now?

205
00:11:17,824 --> 00:11:18,825
[sighs]

206
00:11:21,203 --> 00:11:22,287
[sighs]

207
00:11:30,003 --> 00:11:31,171
Remember?

208
00:11:33,798 --> 00:11:35,300
In 11th grade,

209
00:11:35,383 --> 00:11:38,970
when you had that motorcycle accident,
and I took you to the hospital.

210
00:11:39,554 --> 00:11:40,680
When you woke up you asked,

211
00:11:40,764 --> 00:11:42,849
"Was it you?" And threw a punch at me.

212
00:11:42,933 --> 00:11:45,101
-[chuckles] Geez.
-[Woo-su chuckles]

213
00:11:45,685 --> 00:11:47,771
I thought you were the one
who rammed into me.

214
00:11:47,854 --> 00:11:49,105
[chuckles]

215
00:11:49,189 --> 00:11:50,899
You brought me that porridge
back then, remember?

216
00:11:51,983 --> 00:11:53,276
It was so weird though.

217
00:11:54,069 --> 00:11:57,739
Why would this guy buy me this stuff,
even after I hit him for nothing?

218
00:11:57,822 --> 00:11:59,533
[Gi-jeon] It was mid-winter.

219
00:11:59,616 --> 00:12:01,701
And you were only wearing slippers.

220
00:12:01,785 --> 00:12:03,537
And you looked younger than me.

221
00:12:03,620 --> 00:12:06,122
I just assumed you were struggling.
That's why.

222
00:12:07,916 --> 00:12:11,169
It was the first time anyone had ever
been kind to me for nothing.

223
00:12:11,878 --> 00:12:13,213
It made me feel weird.

224
00:12:15,549 --> 00:12:19,511
I thought I'll end up being a real jerk
if I keep living like this.

225
00:12:20,011 --> 00:12:22,347
Will I ever be able to be
someone like him?

226
00:12:25,183 --> 00:12:28,937
If I hadn't met you back then,
I'd probably be living the same life.

227
00:12:29,521 --> 00:12:31,856
[tender music playing]

228
00:12:32,983 --> 00:12:34,192
[Gi-jeon] Back then,

229
00:12:35,235 --> 00:12:37,153
I just thought you were crazy.

230
00:12:38,530 --> 00:12:40,115
[inhales sharply]

231
00:12:40,198 --> 00:12:42,075
But somehow, I knew I'd see you again.

232
00:12:42,742 --> 00:12:43,743
[stammers] How?

233
00:12:43,827 --> 00:12:44,828
I don't know.

234
00:12:47,247 --> 00:12:48,415
A hunch.

235
00:12:50,917 --> 00:12:52,711
Then I saw this egghead

236
00:12:53,211 --> 00:12:55,922
-during our teacher training orientation.
-[chuckles]

237
00:12:56,006 --> 00:12:58,967
I was so glad to see you.
Weren't you glad as well?

238
00:13:01,469 --> 00:13:04,431
More or less.
He had a pretty dumb look on his face.

239
00:13:04,514 --> 00:13:06,099
-Oh, come on.
-You got that right.

240
00:13:06,766 --> 00:13:08,893
-You're right. He still does.
-[Gi-jeon] Whatever.

241
00:13:08,977 --> 00:13:10,061
Well…

242
00:13:10,854 --> 00:13:13,523
Past or present, it doesn't really matter

243
00:13:14,441 --> 00:13:16,818
which version of you it is,
you're still you.

244
00:13:18,903 --> 00:13:20,572
You just have to live with it.

245
00:13:25,076 --> 00:13:27,621
I must say, Dong-ju is really something.

246
00:13:28,246 --> 00:13:30,248
A street fighter turned over a new leaf

247
00:13:30,332 --> 00:13:33,251
and studied to join our
college of education in two years?

248
00:13:33,335 --> 00:13:34,711
-That's nearly impossible.
-Ridiculous.

249
00:13:34,794 --> 00:13:37,547
-Mmm.
-He was more than capable, but…

250
00:13:38,340 --> 00:13:40,508
the circumstances just didn't favor him.

251
00:13:41,092 --> 00:13:43,720
And where was that? Remember?

252
00:13:43,803 --> 00:13:45,764
When Dong-ju showed his real skills?

253
00:13:45,847 --> 00:13:48,224
-When… When was that?
-The store.

254
00:13:48,308 --> 00:13:49,351
-That's right!
-[chuckles]

255
00:13:49,434 --> 00:13:51,394
It was the first time since
the convenience store, right?

256
00:13:51,478 --> 00:13:52,520
-[chuckles]
-[Dong-ju] Come on.

257
00:13:52,604 --> 00:13:54,481
-I told you not to bring that up.
-[Da-ju] The convenience store.

258
00:13:54,564 --> 00:13:57,776
We were all wasted, walking toward
the convenience store like zombies

259
00:13:57,859 --> 00:13:58,985
to get a cup of noodles.

260
00:13:59,069 --> 00:14:02,364
When those thugs started picking on
that girl that was working there.

261
00:14:06,868 --> 00:14:08,870
[keyboard clacking]

262
00:14:13,625 --> 00:14:15,210
Is this fun for you?

263
00:14:16,503 --> 00:14:17,504
Picking on kids?

264
00:14:17,587 --> 00:14:19,506
-[gasps]
-[grunting]

265
00:14:19,589 --> 00:14:21,049
[intense heroic music playing]

266
00:14:21,132 --> 00:14:23,593
Me? A literature teacher.

267
00:14:23,677 --> 00:14:24,844
[music fades]

268
00:14:24,928 --> 00:14:27,472
[gasps, sighs]

269
00:14:28,640 --> 00:14:31,476
I had no idea
Mr. Yoon could have a secret like that.

270
00:14:32,352 --> 00:14:34,938
He usually hides his true self, but…

271
00:14:35,021 --> 00:14:38,400
But if he has to protect someone,
he fights.

272
00:14:39,401 --> 00:14:41,653
[sighing]

273
00:14:41,736 --> 00:14:44,823
It's coming. It's coming.
I'm feeling inspired.

274
00:14:45,740 --> 00:14:46,908
[tense Western music playing]

275
00:14:46,991 --> 00:14:50,286
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 8

276
00:14:58,294 --> 00:15:00,505
Forget it. So, where is that place?

277
00:15:00,588 --> 00:15:02,132
Their food is so good and creamy.

278
00:15:05,051 --> 00:15:06,886
[rewinding sounds]

279
00:15:09,264 --> 00:15:10,348
Let's go.

280
00:15:14,978 --> 00:15:16,062
Who the hell are you?

281
00:15:17,689 --> 00:15:20,066
Fists aren't meant for hurting people.

282
00:15:20,150 --> 00:15:23,486
They're meant for protecting them.
Haven't you learned?

283
00:15:23,570 --> 00:15:26,489
Damn! So we're playing teacher, are we?

284
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:31,035
-You little--
-[grunting]

285
00:15:31,119 --> 00:15:32,746
[blows landing]

286
00:15:32,829 --> 00:15:34,289
[shrieks]

287
00:15:40,962 --> 00:15:42,297
[thugs coughing]

288
00:15:42,380 --> 00:15:43,673
If I see your faces again,

289
00:15:44,674 --> 00:15:46,259
you're dead meat for real.

290
00:15:48,595 --> 00:15:50,972
Come on. Let's go. Let's go now. Come on.

291
00:15:51,055 --> 00:15:52,390
[grunting]

292
00:15:53,308 --> 00:15:54,392
I was gonna help you,

293
00:15:54,476 --> 00:15:56,436
but it seemed like
you were handling it just fine.

294
00:16:00,273 --> 00:16:01,900
"If I see your faces again,

295
00:16:02,817 --> 00:16:04,861
you're dead meat for real."

296
00:16:06,780 --> 00:16:07,781
[sighs]

297
00:16:08,281 --> 00:16:09,365
Oh, man.

298
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:13,411
He's so cool. So cool.

299
00:16:13,495 --> 00:16:14,496
[chuckles]

300
00:16:15,079 --> 00:16:16,664
[clicks tongue, sighs]

301
00:16:16,748 --> 00:16:20,627
CHAPTER 38:
SIR! I HAVE SOMETHING TO SAY!

302
00:16:20,710 --> 00:16:22,212
[students chattering]

303
00:16:33,014 --> 00:16:34,015
Hi.

304
00:16:45,652 --> 00:16:46,778
What's gotten into her?

305
00:16:46,861 --> 00:16:47,862
Beats me.

306
00:16:48,530 --> 00:16:50,490
-She's scaring me.
-[chuckles]

307
00:16:57,747 --> 00:17:00,250
[class] Hello.

308
00:17:00,333 --> 00:17:03,086
-Mr. Ga, your face.
-What happened?

309
00:17:03,169 --> 00:17:04,921
-Mr. Ga, are you okay?
-Did you fight?

310
00:17:05,004 --> 00:17:06,130
What's going on?

311
00:17:06,214 --> 00:17:09,300
-Are you okay?
-Come on, Mr. Ga, tell us what happened.

312
00:17:09,384 --> 00:17:12,011
Mr. Ga! Mr. Ga, did you get into a fight?

313
00:17:12,095 --> 00:17:13,555
-Tell us.
-[banging on podium]

314
00:17:13,638 --> 00:17:14,722
Quiet.

315
00:17:14,806 --> 00:17:15,849
I'm okay, so don't worry.

316
00:17:15,932 --> 00:17:17,350
-Aw. Really?
-You don't look okay.

317
00:17:17,433 --> 00:17:19,811
-It's time for attendance.
-[clamoring continues]

318
00:17:19,894 --> 00:17:21,479
-Jeon Ji-min.
-Here.

319
00:17:21,563 --> 00:17:22,689
-Oh Ji-ho.
-Here.

320
00:17:22,772 --> 00:17:24,941
-It's worse than I thought it'd be.
-[Woo-su] Kim Ga-yeong.

321
00:17:25,024 --> 00:17:26,901
-[Ga-yeong] Here.
-It looks better than yesterday.

322
00:17:26,985 --> 00:17:29,779
-Oh, you guys…
-[Woo-su] Hong Su-min.

323
00:17:29,863 --> 00:17:30,905
You're friends again?

324
00:17:30,989 --> 00:17:32,615
-[Woo-su] Jeon Chae-won.
-[chuckles softly]

325
00:17:32,699 --> 00:17:34,033
-Well, when weren't we?
-Im Su-yeon.

326
00:17:34,117 --> 00:17:35,827
-Here.
-[chuckles softly]

327
00:17:37,453 --> 00:17:39,247
-Lee Eun-ji.
-Here.

328
00:17:39,330 --> 00:17:40,707
-Choi Hye-jeong.
-Here.

329
00:17:43,042 --> 00:17:45,128
Good luck with your class today. Bye.

330
00:17:45,753 --> 00:17:47,630
[class] Thank you.

331
00:17:47,714 --> 00:17:49,549
[chattering]

332
00:17:49,632 --> 00:17:51,009
Why is he always like that?

333
00:17:53,094 --> 00:17:54,095
Mr. Ga!

334
00:18:00,101 --> 00:18:02,353
I'm sorry. Because of me, you…

335
00:18:05,732 --> 00:18:06,733
Are you okay?

336
00:18:08,610 --> 00:18:09,611
Yes.

337
00:18:11,279 --> 00:18:13,281
That's good. Pay attention in class.

338
00:18:15,283 --> 00:18:16,910
[gentle music playing]

339
00:18:16,993 --> 00:18:17,994
Okay.

340
00:18:32,926 --> 00:18:33,927
Hmm?

341
00:18:35,345 --> 00:18:36,429
Hello.

342
00:18:36,512 --> 00:18:37,513
-Hi.
-Hello.

343
00:18:46,064 --> 00:18:47,649
[music fades]

344
00:18:47,732 --> 00:18:49,233
Are you okay?

345
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:52,946
I am. I just have to reconsider.

346
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:59,452
But look… [stammering]
…he's seriously different now.

347
00:18:59,535 --> 00:19:00,703
I mean that.

348
00:19:00,787 --> 00:19:03,915
I really think Mr. Yoon is
a good man now, actually.

349
00:19:05,083 --> 00:19:07,335
Never mind. My opinion doesn't matter.

350
00:19:08,002 --> 00:19:10,338
Your feelings are more important. [sighs]

351
00:19:10,838 --> 00:19:13,216
If you're over him,
that's perfectly fine too.

352
00:19:13,841 --> 00:19:14,842
I understand.

353
00:19:16,511 --> 00:19:18,012
Who said I was over him?

354
00:19:20,223 --> 00:19:21,224
Isn't that what you meant?

355
00:19:23,101 --> 00:19:25,103
No. It's my turn now.

356
00:19:26,104 --> 00:19:27,814
From here on out, it's on me.

357
00:19:27,897 --> 00:19:30,984
No matter what hits us,
I'll keep Dong-ju safe.

358
00:19:31,526 --> 00:19:32,527
And out of trouble.

359
00:19:32,610 --> 00:19:34,612
[cheerful music playing]

360
00:19:34,696 --> 00:19:35,697
Go-ya.

361
00:19:36,447 --> 00:19:38,700
To do that,
I need to get into a good college.

362
00:19:38,783 --> 00:19:40,451
And build a successful life.

363
00:19:40,535 --> 00:19:42,870
I need to be someone
Dong-ju can truly rely on.

364
00:19:44,455 --> 00:19:48,376
Actually, if I'm going to protect Dong-ju,
I'm going to have to step it up.

365
00:19:50,378 --> 00:19:51,587
The CSAT.

366
00:19:52,130 --> 00:19:55,466
I have to get a good CSAT score
so I'll have more college options.

367
00:19:55,550 --> 00:19:56,551
[sighs]

368
00:19:57,301 --> 00:19:58,302
You know what?

369
00:19:59,012 --> 00:20:01,055
This must be why
I've been single since birth.

370
00:20:01,723 --> 00:20:02,724
Hmm?

371
00:20:02,807 --> 00:20:05,018
All I want is for that person…

372
00:20:05,601 --> 00:20:09,397
I mean, I just want my crush to
like me back, that's all I want.

373
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:11,816
I want him to fall for me
and be head over heels for me

374
00:20:11,899 --> 00:20:13,901
even if I don't do anything in particular.

375
00:20:15,278 --> 00:20:16,279
[sighs]

376
00:20:16,863 --> 00:20:19,949
But all I do is whine like a child

377
00:20:20,950 --> 00:20:22,285
and get jealous too,

378
00:20:22,869 --> 00:20:25,204
instead of trying to become
someone attractive first.

379
00:20:30,251 --> 00:20:32,587
You're already gorgeous, okay?

380
00:20:32,670 --> 00:20:35,256
[upbeat K-pop song playing]

381
00:20:35,339 --> 00:20:36,340
Okay?

382
00:20:37,967 --> 00:20:40,261
[inhales deeply, sighs]

383
00:20:40,344 --> 00:20:41,804
What do you think I should do?

384
00:20:43,765 --> 00:20:46,225
-[sighs]
-[sighs]

385
00:20:48,478 --> 00:20:49,479
Just tell him.

386
00:20:51,981 --> 00:20:53,691
He might leave for the States.

387
00:20:55,109 --> 00:20:56,569
-Tell him?
-Mm-hmm.

388
00:20:58,237 --> 00:21:02,158
[sighs] I don't know. How do you do that?

389
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:05,912
Okay. Look into his eyes.

390
00:21:05,995 --> 00:21:07,455
To show you mean it.

391
00:21:07,538 --> 00:21:09,207
You have to make eye contact

392
00:21:09,874 --> 00:21:11,793
and stare right at him…

393
00:21:11,876 --> 00:21:13,211
[amusing music playing]

394
00:21:13,294 --> 00:21:15,129
…for three seconds.

395
00:21:17,882 --> 00:21:19,008
Ow.

396
00:21:19,717 --> 00:21:21,302
-[groans] Oh, come on.
-[chuckles]

397
00:21:21,385 --> 00:21:23,304
How am I supposed to do that?

398
00:21:23,387 --> 00:21:24,889
Do you want to tell him
how you feel or not?

399
00:21:24,972 --> 00:21:26,891
[sighs, sniffles]

400
00:21:27,642 --> 00:21:28,976
I do want to.

401
00:21:29,060 --> 00:21:31,020
Then listen to me. Three seconds.

402
00:21:33,856 --> 00:21:35,274
Okay, I'll give it a try.

403
00:21:35,358 --> 00:21:37,985
Look into his eyes for three seconds
and say, "I like you."

404
00:21:38,069 --> 00:21:39,612
That's all you need to do.

405
00:21:42,532 --> 00:21:44,617
Even if it's someone you have
zero feelings for,

406
00:21:44,700 --> 00:21:46,786
do you know what happens
when you hear that?

407
00:21:47,703 --> 00:21:50,790
It makes you waver.
Well, it really shakes you.

408
00:21:51,374 --> 00:21:52,834
-Waver?
-Mm-hmm.

409
00:21:52,917 --> 00:21:54,585
He'll waver. For sure.

410
00:21:54,669 --> 00:21:56,087
That's the way it is for men.

411
00:21:57,588 --> 00:22:00,883
First snow, remember?
Always goes straight ahead.

412
00:22:02,552 --> 00:22:04,554
Okay. Straight ahead.

413
00:22:04,637 --> 00:22:06,222
Don't waste your time
waiting and hesitating.

414
00:22:06,305 --> 00:22:07,557
Take no detours, okay?

415
00:22:08,307 --> 00:22:11,269
Okay.
Then where do you think I should do it?

416
00:22:11,352 --> 00:22:13,187
You have an after-school class today.
After that!

417
00:22:14,438 --> 00:22:15,439
Today?

418
00:22:16,649 --> 00:22:18,109
Today… [inhales sharply]

419
00:22:19,402 --> 00:22:22,113
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

420
00:22:22,780 --> 00:22:25,283
So, the function graph
would be organized like this, right?

421
00:22:25,908 --> 00:22:27,702
-What should I say first?
-The x-coordinates of

422
00:22:27,785 --> 00:22:29,745
the intersections between y equals f(x)

423
00:22:29,829 --> 00:22:32,415
-and y equals k to have one positive…
-Mr. Ga, I…

424
00:22:32,498 --> 00:22:35,084
…and two negative values, the range for k

425
00:22:35,168 --> 00:22:37,753
-must be between minus eight to zero.
-The truth is, I have…

426
00:22:37,837 --> 00:22:40,756
Once you plot it,
it becomes intuitively clear, okay?

427
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:42,758
-Let's stop here today. Good job.
-[whimpers]

428
00:22:42,842 --> 00:22:43,843
[class] Thank you.

429
00:22:43,926 --> 00:22:45,386
Huh? What the…

430
00:22:45,469 --> 00:22:46,554
It's over already?

431
00:22:46,637 --> 00:22:47,638
[student] Good-bye.

432
00:22:49,056 --> 00:22:50,349
[groans, inhales shakily]

433
00:22:51,475 --> 00:22:54,520
Okay, let's wait until
all the girls leave first.

434
00:22:56,981 --> 00:22:58,858
[groans, breathes shakily]

435
00:23:01,527 --> 00:23:02,403
You leaving?

436
00:23:04,405 --> 00:23:06,115
I am. I'm leaving.

437
00:23:06,199 --> 00:23:07,200
Mr. Ga!

438
00:23:09,076 --> 00:23:10,203
[hopeful music playing]

439
00:23:10,286 --> 00:23:12,538
[breathing shakily]
Now is the time. It has to be now.

440
00:23:19,420 --> 00:23:20,504
You got…

441
00:23:23,174 --> 00:23:25,885
your new glasses. [chuckles]

442
00:23:25,968 --> 00:23:29,055
[inhales deeply, shudders] Oh, no. No.

443
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:34,685
[comical music playing]

444
00:23:36,145 --> 00:23:37,396
[groans]

445
00:23:38,481 --> 00:23:39,523
[sighs]

446
00:23:40,107 --> 00:23:41,567
Come on. You can do it, Eui-ju!

447
00:23:41,651 --> 00:23:42,735
Wait!

448
00:23:44,779 --> 00:23:46,948
[whimpering]

449
00:23:48,866 --> 00:23:50,243
No, it has to be today.

450
00:23:50,326 --> 00:23:52,036
Either I do it today
or I'm never gonna do it.

451
00:24:03,756 --> 00:24:06,050
Mr. Ga! Mr. Ga. Wait, Mr. Ga.

452
00:24:06,676 --> 00:24:09,512
Sir, I have something to tell you!
Wait just a moment.

453
00:24:09,595 --> 00:24:11,889
Wait, Mr. Ga. [panting] Hold on.

454
00:24:11,973 --> 00:24:13,599
[panting]

455
00:24:15,893 --> 00:24:17,103
[pants] Just a second.

456
00:24:23,067 --> 00:24:24,110
What is it, huh?

457
00:24:25,111 --> 00:24:26,112
I…

458
00:24:31,659 --> 00:24:32,827
I…

459
00:24:32,910 --> 00:24:34,912
[hopeful, tender music playing]

460
00:24:41,085 --> 00:24:42,086
I…

461
00:25:06,444 --> 00:25:07,945
Yeo Eui-ju, follow me.

462
00:25:08,029 --> 00:25:09,030
Why is Math so strict?

463
00:25:09,113 --> 00:25:12,283
[Eui-ju] He's just doing it his way,
isn't he? That might actually be fair.

464
00:25:12,366 --> 00:25:14,118
[Ha-su] There's this web novel
with characters

465
00:25:14,201 --> 00:25:16,746
who are almost identical to
our Korean lit, Math, PE,

466
00:25:16,829 --> 00:25:18,289
and Japanese language teachers.

467
00:25:18,372 --> 00:25:20,207
[groans]
I'm dying to know who the writer is.

468
00:25:20,291 --> 00:25:21,625
You're done for.

469
00:25:21,709 --> 00:25:23,127
I think you should know who it is.

470
00:25:23,210 --> 00:25:25,296
-It's Yeo Eui-ju.
-What are you talking about?

471
00:25:25,379 --> 00:25:27,214
-[Go-ya] Is it you?
-Actually…

472
00:25:27,298 --> 00:25:28,841
-Go-ya, what happened is--
-This is nuts.

473
00:25:28,924 --> 00:25:30,468
[Young-hee] You'll be expelled.

474
00:25:30,551 --> 00:25:32,386
[Eui-ju]
Just act like you don't know, okay?

475
00:25:32,470 --> 00:25:34,472
I don't want you getting in trouble
because of me.

476
00:25:34,555 --> 00:25:37,391
Hello, everyone. This is Imuk.
